Scan a IP  -> nmap IP
Scan a host  -> nmap hostname
Scan range of IPs  -> nmap 192.168.1.1-20
Scan subnet  -> nmap 192.168.1.0/24
Scan from file  -> nmap -iL list.txt
Scan single port  -> nmap -p 22 IP
Scan range of ports  -> nmap -p 1-100 IP
Scan 100 common ports (fast)  -> nmap -F IP
Scan all 65535 ports  -> nmap -p- IP
Scan using TCP connect  -> nmap -sT IP
Scan using TCP SYN scan  -> nmap -sS IP
Scan UDP port  -> nmap -sU -p 
Save in all formats  -> 	nmap -oA outputfile IP
Detect OS and Services  ->	nmap -A IP
Standard service detection	 -> nmap -sV IP
